        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 12:31PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 1230 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Favonia, or near Ceres, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Wytheville...
Max Meadows...
Gunton Park...
Fort Chiswell...
Favonia...
and Coleman Store.
</description>
        <instruction>Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
